findings.recommendation:
Non-blocking for Phase 2 — the KDoc-documented workaround + AC-13/AC-18 smoke is an acceptable compromise given Robolectric's rasterisation gap. Consider for a future phase (or tracked as tech-debt): add a minimal `core-runtime/src/androidTest/kotlin/app/sanctum/machina/core/common/MediaUtilsInstrumentationTest.kt` that runs on device/emulator and seeds pixel markers. Shape:

  @RunWith(AndroidJUnit4::class)
  class MediaUtilsInstrumentationTest {
    @Test fun rotateBitmap_rotate180_swapsCornerPixels() {
      val src = Bitmap.createBitmap(4, 8, Bitmap.Config.ARGB_8888).apply {
        setPixel(0, 0, Color.RED)
        setPixel(3, 7, Color.BLUE)
      }
      val out = rotateBitmap(src, ExifInterface.ORIENTATION_ROTATE_180)
      assertEquals(Color.BLUE, out.getPixel(0, 0))
      assertEquals(Color.RED,  out.getPixel(3, 7))
    }
    // Analogous tests for FLIP_HORIZONTAL / FLIP_VERTICAL / TRANSPOSE / TRANSVERSE
  }

Tech-spec D20 notes 'instrumentation androidTest rejected — solo dev не гоняет regularly', so this is consistent with the existing trade-off — leave deferred unless Phase 3 introduces automated device runs.

Non-blocking. If included, the cost is bounded — write the seed via File.writeBytes, not via repeated errorLog.e() calls. Shape:

  @Test fun rotation_overSizeThreshold_renamesAndClearsLog() = runBlocking {
    val dir = File(context.filesDir, "logs").apply { mkdirs() }
    File(dir, "errors.log").writeBytes(ByteArray(2 * 1024 * 1024 + 1))
    File(dir, "errors.log.1").writeText("old rotated content")  // verify it gets deleted
    errorLog.e("inference", "trigger-rotate")
    assertTrue(File(dir, "errors.log.1").exists())
    // After rotation, a new errors.log does NOT exist (rename moved it); next e() would recreate it.
    // Assert old rotated content was overwritten by the rename:
    assertTrue(File(dir, "errors.log.1").readText().contains("trigger-rotate"))
  }

The 2 MB write is ~100 ms on modern SSDs — a one-off cost in the suite. Alternative: keep deferred and note in decisions.md so Phase 3 picks it up. Either choice is defensible — flagging so it's not lost.
